route.soft_comment: Kaboooom! Feels great to do something on my honest second GO that neither Chris Sharma nor Adam Ondra onsighted. Even jimmy "I have a manlier beard" Webb didn't do the moves on this rig. I just don't understand why people line up for short dumpy jug hauls like prohibition, while stellar test pieces like this exist in Colorado. The new la sportiva grip rubber really helped me campus through the crux on this one - especially in the heat! Glad to finally meet my life quota by climbing 14d and psyched to have a few more hard climbs on deck.

route.name: Blackened
route.fair_comment: Watts guide indicates this singular line of bolts has two route names and two route grades depending on if you climb on the right side of the bolts or the left. I had planned to pontificate on this blatent dumbassery until I realized the unlimited potential in 8a points this allows me. My plan now is to get a 4fer for every route I do. One for the path of least resistance, one each for the left and right and one for what I call 'the zig zag' - And then, after I exhaust that shit, the retro-chipping starts.

route.fair_comment: First redpoint in almost 2 and half years since last tying up my shoes. Feels amazing to be climbing!

route.name: Five Easy Pieces

route.name: Up For Grabs

route.soft_comment: Très belle voie super variée

route.name: Bad Moon Rising

route.fair_comment: Top Sight. Very fun smithy route with fun crux coming over roof.

route.name: Riptide
route.hard_comment: warmup... I feel like there must be a broken hold up top.

route.name: Latin Lover
route.hard_comment: Consistent...
route.fair_comment: Alzheimers onsight. Kind of enjoyed this one!

route.name: Blasphemy

route.name: Cosmos
route.hard_comment: scaryy..

route.name: Barbecue the pope
route.hard_comment: The hardest 10b in the world!! But such a fun route.

route.name: Rawhide

route.name: Wedding Day
route.hard_comment: Technical.
route.fair_comment: Tricky off the ground, not a gimme-.10b

route.name: Gumby

route.name: Tsunami
route.hard_comment: One of the best at smith
route.fair_comment: well set, like a gym route!
route.soft_comment: Jug huall.

route.name: Eye of the Beholder

route.name: Chain Reaction

route.soft_comment: Best climb there. So Far...

route.name: Fish and Chips
route.hard_comment: Amazing exposure / position.
route.fair_comment: pretty fun for the grade with some nice lieback position

route.name: Moondance
route.hard_comment: Technical the whole way.

route.fair_comment: West Coast version of Flyin Hawaiian with like a million more palming and stemming moves. I finally did something before Brian! His goal is to climb something that has never been onsighted, mine was to onsight something he didn't onsight. Woohoo! I found my style.

route.name: Last Waltz
route.hard_comment: . 8 tries. It felt like 7b+ on the send but like 9a every other time. 10 days in Smith 1 send. SPRiNG BREAK!

route.name: Middle Aged Vandals

route.name: Powder up the Nose

route.name: Ride the Lightning

route.name: Full magic light

route.name: Sting like a bee

route.name: Hissing Llamas

route.name: Boys in the hood

route.soft_comment: Atypical but very fun

route.name: Tricks For You
route.soft_comment: Techy

route.name: Mater Hater
route.soft_comment: Fun.

route.name: The Burden of Immortality

route.name: Vitamin K

route.name: Tutu Man

route.name: Limestoned

route.name: I Just Do Eyes

route.hard_comment: crrrrack
route.soft_comment: Fun pseudo-warmup

route.name: Unsubstantiated Propaganda

route.name: Godfather 1
route.soft_comment: Felt easy, 10b? Fun jug haul

route.name: July Jihad
route.fair_comment: ALMOST 2nd go, punted on the second to last move. Great route though
route.soft_comment: Cool overhung crux

route.hard_comment: boulder problem!

route.soft_comment: hard start, then not so bad. EKV is better

route.fair_comment: Very short on amazing rock. Exhausted last day in TS.

route.name: Number One Enemy

route.name: Always Keep It Loaded

route.name: Joy of Heresy

route.name: The Caverns
route.fair_comment: Following is bitch work until your partner makes you lead the last pitch because you’re both too scared. Most of the pitches on this route were wet. Bouldering does not teach you to climb wet slab, hand jam or place gear. Scary but the most fun I've had climbing in a while.

route.name: Steck-Salathe
route.hard_comment: So amazing, 13 pitches

route.name: The Moratorium
route.fair_comment: One of my favorite routes in the valley. Two pitches of perfect 10d dihedral cracks leads to the crux pitch. Really thin finger locks through a steep dihedral leads to the anchor. Amazing!

route.name: The Crucifix
route.hard_comment: The Crucifix is 6 pitches - we simulclimbed the first half of the NEB of Higher (500 feet) to the ledge to the start of this route. Awesome day - great climbing, one of the bast in the Valley. The guide book gives it a 12b rating.
route.fair_comment: Every pitch is hard for different reasons. Worked the crux once then did it next go. Barely hung on for the rest of the route. Took longer than we expected ... watched the sun set from the summit of Higher Cathedral. Thanks Colin for a great adventure!

route.name: Serenity Sons
route.fair_comment: Serenity Crack->Sons of Yesterday, one route IMO. Super-fun, sustained splitters.

route.name: Uncle Fanny
route.fair_comment: Bonne mise en jambe. Sortie cheminée pas facile avec 15kg au cul. 2/3 assez fin.

route.name: English Breakfast Crack
route.fair_comment: P1 5.9 30m OW, 3 pieces. P2 10c 20m 6 pieces. Arch Rock at its finest again. Gorgeous bottom OW pitch that should be the reason to do this climb. The P2 dihedral is nice as well and holds a green alien + a little surprise just below the anchor.

route.name: Nickel Bag
route.fair_comment: awesome power moves to a brief slab!

route.name: Desperado
route.fair_comment: Fell at bolt one, came down, sent barely. Brought a #3 Camalot with a draw for the roof.

route.name: Crucifix
route.fair_comment: Grade IV bottom to top. Simuled the bottom of NE Butt to get to the start. 10c fisting pitch one of the best 240ft long splitter you could climb on. Gets you ready for the very real 10c OW following pitch. Braille Book simul onsite same day.

route.name: The Good Book

route.name: West Face of El Capitan
route.hard_comment: Wicked and very varied climbing than just keeps on coming at you! Great day out!

route.name: Roadside Attraction

route.name: El Nino

route.name: Generator Crack

route.name: Revival

route.name: Astroman

route.name: Separate reality

route.name: New wave
route.hard_comment: Gnarly.

route.name: Climb like a Girl

route.soft_comment: miraculous i sent considering how wet it was

route.fair_comment: got really good locals beta! thanks jessie

route.fair_comment: So pscyched about this route that I started an 8a account :) It is 'the line' for sure. In my opinion the straightest, most direct and most difficult way to climb Golden, It cuts out all the big rests and tackles the whole cave: Start on Space shuttle, do the big move left at the crux and then blast straight up the steepness, through the golden direct start and into golden. The best sport route I have ever done and my hardest so far. Lots of tries lots of effort.

route.hard_comment: I thought this route was spanny, slick, and insecure. Some new bolts would be nice, too. Still, if you are looking for a short bouldery route in this grade, look no further.

route.name: Jealous God
route.hard_comment: feels like the hardest of the 12a's at si. not an ultra classic, but a decent bouldery sequence to finish. took 3 burns.
route.fair_comment: the chain reaction of little si but easier

route.name: Flatliner
route.hard_comment: Finally...2 goes today, I think around 8 total. Sick of taking and grabbing nylon slings when I got scared of the fall. Good to have this one done. Two 13c's in two days. Psyched. Extended going down next, and hopefully Pornstar by the time Worlds comes around.

route.name: Californicator
route.hard_comment: Burly enduro route...my hardest to date! CHRONIC (which this shares 1st 7 clips of) is NEXT. "I call as my heart grows faint; lead me to the rock that is higher than I." Psalm 61:2
route.fair_comment: onsighted the cali section but had done chronic. date?

route.name: Lizard Prince
route.hard_comment: 3rd go! so psyched! I'm not sure about the 8a+, though...After having sent it, again to get on Lizard King, I still find this line stout. the moves off the chronic anchors are hard. Upgrading to 8a hard. :)
route.soft_comment: Like a 12a extension of Chronic...I've done the first part before, but today was my first time on Lizard. Guide book says 13c...but I don't think so. Doesn't make it harder. I did Chronic 3 times today, and this one twice. FITNESS CHECK

route.name: Dairy freeze
route.hard_comment: Karma restored... Excellent route, one of the most diverse I've done at WW1, loved the slab, dyno(my beta), and even the crux felt good today!

route.name: Dr. Evil
route.hard_comment: its about time. this one was very hard for me. what a relentless route. mega classics at little si. thats all we got man, dude.
route.fair_comment: Symphony of small holds. Climbs much better than it looks.

route.name: Black is all we feel
route.hard_comment: Bouldery. Bolted a little strange; with the obligatory #2 camalot placement. Fun climbing though.
route.fair_comment: Fun, 5.10 to v6 roof. Just needed some beta and sent second go today!!

route.name: Oval Orifice
route.hard_comment: an overlooked jem

route.name: Propaganda
route.hard_comment: I guess I'll register this as 12c, even though everyone knows this is HARD 12d. Surprised myself with the quick send today.

route.name: Mambo Jambo
route.hard_comment: 10b trad onsight, I skipped the top bolts for an all trad climb. excellent!
route.fair_comment: Beautiful climb...one of my proudest trad sends. A monster in the closet that's finally been dealt with (I took a whipper on it a year ago that shook me up :).

route.name: False God
route.hard_comment: false idol into jealous god = hard 12a. fun climbing
route.fair_comment: Yeah it's a link up. But a good one, maybe the best on this wall.

route.name: Black Plague
route.hard_comment: 4th go. Classic power endurance with one rest. Nice one Josh. A few enhanced holds... but, still fun.

route.name: Gerbil Rising
route.hard_comment: An impressively stacked line linking Gerbil Killer into Flatliner. Definitely harder than through Psycho. Almost done with the crag...

route.name: Gerbal Rising
route.hard_comment: better than flatliner. also did porn star today. check that fitness

route.name: Coup D'Etat
route.fair_comment: Picture here. 7th go. 1st try of day. Sent it putting draws up on 2nd half. My first 13a at Jackson Falls!
route.soft_comment: V6/7 to 5.10 climbing

route.name: Mighty Mouse
route.soft_comment: Super fun for a 3 bolt climb. Great pockets.

route.name: Cranial Implosion
route.soft_comment: Very short, but last move felt hard. 3rd 12 of the day!

route.name: Xterminator
route.fair_comment: 5.12a Thanks to Calvin for the excellent beta.
route.soft_comment: Pretty fun, great beta from T Raw, Biggest Jugs at Jackson. Easier than Generator X tho

route.name: Darwin's Theory
route.fair_comment: 5.12b Short, slightly overhanging, crux is long move off crimp to sloper-jug.

route.name: Rain Dog
route.fair_comment: 2nd go this year, one move wonder, no anchors, bad bolting, not fun. Last route on tower for me, but new 12d? being bolted same day.
route.soft_comment: Crazy lichen covered mantle in a tree. No anchors. Walked around a dead cedar tree and came down.

route.name: Flinging Hog
route.fair_comment: 5.11a - a classic at jackson, great climbing through multiple bulges

route.name: Piss Ant
route.fair_comment: Real fun route. make sure to use the left most bolt near the top, when you have the choice (for the 11 b).

route.name: Cherrio Bowl
route.fair_comment: 5.10a - so sweet. love it. one of the best in its grade
route.soft_comment: Ash belayed

route.name: Lothlorien
route.fair_comment: toprope os. Did as R rated sport lead later.

route.name: Umbrella Girl
route.soft_comment: 5.12a - looks short, but the pump sets in fast! great movement, flows really well. figured out a sweet finger lock hold for my redpoint crux.

route.name: Extinguisher
route.hard_comment: Hard deadpoints to good pockets
route.soft_comment: First 12a! Third try.

route.name: Shock Therapy
route.fair_comment: now I never have to get on it ever again.
route.soft_comment: My rope ripped through the sheath and then one strand of the core. Scary Junky route.

route.name: Slabstick Comedy
route.soft_comment: Third go, runout after 2nd bolt. Scary but not bad.

route.name: Orion
route.fair_comment: Fun slab route, very challenging start.

route.name: Shorty the Pimp
route.fair_comment: Very cool crux! about 10 goes. Hangin' the drizzles. Sweetness.
route.soft_comment: Short crux. First 13a!

route.name: No Dogs Allowed
route.fair_comment: bring a sling for the runout finish, brief crux at the bottom.
route.soft_comment: cool thin/reachy boulder problem start. huge jug plates to finish. bring 4foot sling

route.name: Red Corvette
route.soft_comment: some solid beta from a local

route.name: Voice
route.fair_comment: 2nd go today after 1 burn a year ago. sweet.

route.name: Spits or Swallows
route.fair_comment: 5.12a This route has actually cleaned up quite a bit. Not as chossy as it once was.
route.soft_comment: Should have ended at the lip... Would be a better route.

route.name: The Reckoning
route.soft_comment: 5.12a - feels great to be back in the game 6 months post baby. one of my favs at the falls.

route.name: Velvet Green
route.hard_comment: Fingery and Hard.
route.soft_comment: easier than hidden treasure imo

route.name: Everybody needs friends
route.fair_comment: Short and fun; pumpier than its length would suggest
route.soft_comment: 3rd go. Psyched. on the softer end of 12a but very fun. Go to the jug to before clipping the anchors.

route.name: Remove la Ropa
route.fair_comment: VIDEO. Picture. Bouldery route with a steep start.
route.soft_comment: One well defined crux set in much easier territory.

route.name: Industry
route.fair_comment: Awesome bouldery route. Would like to boulder it someday...
route.soft_comment: Great route if you have power, but poor endurance.

route.name: Here come the snakes
route.hard_comment: Definition of a THUG HAUL
route.fair_comment: super classic roof. big moves to big jugs. stared at this one for a long time before finally getting on it, glad i finally got around to it
route.soft_comment: 5th go. Being tall forsure helps on this one. No need to cut feet. Due to a miscommunication, i proceeded to send this twice back to back in order to clean it. Fitness...

route.name: Viking Blood
route.fair_comment: Killer crimpers up a perfect wall! One of the best at Jfalls I think!

route.name: Tasmanian Devil
route.fair_comment: crux is not touching the damn tree. when the tree goes, the climb will be classic.
route.soft_comment: lower end of 12b I think. Definitely more fun than i thought it'd be.

route.name: Detox Mountain
route.fair_comment: Awesome route. Just needed to take it easy. I guess I do have some endurance...Cro-Magnon next weekend?
route.soft_comment: Travis can pick them. Fabulous climbing on gently overhanging terrain

route.name: Cro-Magnon Warrior
route.soft_comment: Third Go! First 12b, same day I hurt my finger.

route.name: Hidden treasure
route.soft_comment: First redpoint of a 12 second go! Soft if your tall.

route.name: Who needs friends?

route.name: Earthbound Misfit

route.name: The Farmer
route.fair_comment: 3rd go. Cool powerful crux on iron edges.

route.name: The Garden Route
route.fair_comment: 5.10a route on right side of Sleef Peak slab.

route.name: Cut throat

route.name: Emperor of the North

route.name: Earthbound Misfits

route.name: Captain Crunch

route.name: Lasso the Vulture
route.fair_comment: 5.11a technical slab up to "birth canal" chimney.

route.name: Kill Bill

route.name: Condor
route.fair_comment: 5.11c Big iron flakes up to thin arete.

route.name: The Feathered Serpent

route.name: King Snake

route.name: Fancy Feet
route.fair_comment: The 2nd bolt begs to be stepped on... don't do it

route.name: Express Checkout Line
route.fair_comment: Slopey, long, spooky first couple bolts. careful.

route.name: Iniquity

route.name: Umbrella Girls
route.fair_comment: Happy to stick the deadpoint move off the ground! Hard one for me.

route.name: Cougar Love
route.fair_comment: 5.11c Blew the flash after completing all the cruxes. Technical climbing.

route.name: Belching Fiance
route.fair_comment: 5.12a Walked up it, first go on second day of trying.

route.name: Stray Dog
route.hard_comment: Techy slab highsteps. Interesting movement.
route.fair_comment: wet bottom, nearly blew it up high.

route.name: Hugs and Kisses (XOXO)
route.fair_comment: 5.10b Cool overhanging jug fest that jacked up Chrissy's knee.

route.name: The stain
route.fair_comment: first 11d 5 tries beautiful line wet often

route.name: Huecool
route.fair_comment: Picturesque with falls flowing next to you.

route.name: Zapped
route.fair_comment: Rainy day climb! Short and crimpy.

route.name: Tin Man
route.fair_comment: Probably has the hardest move of the 3 short routes on the wall.

route.name: King's Jester

route.name: The Drifter
route.fair_comment: Did on toprope the summer before.

route.name: Gobble Juice

route.name: Split Decision

route.name: Zambezi
route.fair_comment: Congo Spray right variation. Similar difficulty

route.name: Master Marley
route.fair_comment: Cool climb. Only hard part is right at the first bolt.

route.name: Energizer
route.fair_comment: i fell off the last move a few times!

route.name: Psychotherapy
route.fair_comment: Overhung and pumpy. Incredibly difficult to read the sequences and holds from below

route.name: Lovely Arete
route.hard_comment: 5.11a? Hard for the grade. Be careful of the boulder behind you.
route.fair_comment: Beautiful arete with thought provoking moves.

route.name: Lost Innocence
route.hard_comment: Beautiful line
route.fair_comment: Can't lose what you never had...

route.name: Cheerio Bowl
route.soft_comment: Wierd start.... awesome top

route.name: Fashionably Late
route.fair_comment: 5.11a - don't miss this one. surprisingly pumpy for such a short crux through some neat incut crimps

route.name: Wild at Heart
route.fair_comment: 5.10d One of the best routes at the grade I've ever done.

route.name: XOXO
route.hard_comment: 5.10b - hard crux for the grade. very fun finishing section

route.name: Frizzle fry
route.hard_comment: Short power problem. I suck at this stuff!
route.soft_comment: short routes here. good grit.

route.name: Galaxy 500
route.hard_comment: Powerful start, then tech. slab climb. Rated 12a/b.
route.fair_comment: First go was very dirty and scary. Had fun figuring out the beta. Congrats to Mark on the flash!

route.name: Generator X
route.hard_comment: Fell of the chains on my onsight!
route.fair_comment: Tried a few summers ago and couldn't send. Easily went this time ;)

route.name: The Vow
route.hard_comment: hard to do in 90 degree weather and pig sweat humidity
route.fair_comment: The book that I'm publishing said this is the least onsited route at Jackson Falls so I put the pressure on and connected.

route.name: Venom
route.hard_comment: Flashed on top-rope, sent on lead shortly after

route.name: X Factor
route.hard_comment: Fell below the chains on my flash attempt a while back.. Got it while hanging the draws this trip!

route.name: Little Johnny Jewel
route.hard_comment: 5.11b A little sharp. Hard for the grade. Nice onsight Yoli!
route.fair_comment: 5.11b - technical face climbing, difficult start. great route!

route.name: Goin' Rogue
route.hard_comment: Fever send while I had the flu! 3rd try this year. Tried it one day last year at the end of a day. V5/6 bouldering for 3 bolts then easier climbing.

route.name: Bursting Out
route.hard_comment: 5.12b One of the best climbs at the Falls. Very difficult for me. Has a little bit of everything. Enjoyed working this one. Took multiple trips to get the send.

route.name: Who Let the Snakes Out
route.hard_comment: 5.10b? This route is pretty hard for 5.10b.
route.fair_comment: A pretty fun warm up and nice addition to the wall.

route.name: Alaska
route.fair_comment: Not really one of my favorites. Glad to have it off of the tick list atleast

route.name: Unclaimed
route.fair_comment: (Left of Lothlorien). PG/R rated sport lead

route.name: Honeynut Girl
route.fair_comment: Easy 11c with pockety crux w/ lots of options.

route.name: Delirious
route.fair_comment: Surprisingly good for a 5.9+ that probably never gets done.

route.name: The Munchkin
route.hard_comment: With Bernard.

route.name: Tons of Fun
route.soft_comment: 5.10c - first lead outside after a 1 year pregnancy/baby/summer hiatus

route.name: Lucky Charms
route.fair_comment: 5.11c Such a great climb. Thanks goes to Calvin for hanging draws and sussing out the beta!

route.name: Puff
route.hard_comment: Good for a shorty

route.name: Team Honda
route.hard_comment: An outstanding route

route.name: The Twist
route.hard_comment: 5.11c Fun climb. I totally goofed the beta for this one. I probably made it 2 letter grades harder for myself.
route.fair_comment: first 11c ever 3 tries girlfriend go posion ivy on her crotch and still stayed the whole week Thanks Carrie

route.name: Congo Spray
route.hard_comment: One pretty hard move surrounded by very fun climbing.
route.fair_comment: Very nice moves! And man is that sandstone good.
route.soft_comment: Fun route. Flows nicely when you know where the holds are.(Juju)

route.name: Barbarians at the Gate
route.fair_comment: My 50th 5.12 at Jackson Falls. Second try this year, tried it twice many years ago. Painful mono traverse, nice sustained top.

route.name: Working Class
route.hard_comment: Apparently there used to be a big flake near the top that broke so it may now be harder?

route.name: Blue Velvet
route.fair_comment: 5.11c Great route. hard down low, w/ tough mantle at top.

route.name: Raging Intensity
route.hard_comment: Third go, almost second. One of the hidden gems of the falls!
route.fair_comment: If your in the area definitely get on it. Diamond in the ruff. Balancy on awesome features

route.name: Three Hour Tour
route.hard_comment: Slab traverse. Better back clean it. Unique climb

route.name: Flappin Jack
route.hard_comment: With Natie and Barb. A rough trip.

route.name: Dos Hombres
route.hard_comment: Mossy, but a good way to put draws on Viking Blood.

route.name: Inner Pit Bull
route.hard_comment: 2nd ascent. hard 12d?

route.name: Balance of Power
route.hard_comment: This route is incredible! I enjoyed every minute I spent working on this rig. A super satisfying send. Hard 12c, maybe soft 12d?
route.fair_comment: Skip crux bolt for sure. Super fun.

route.name: Cocktail Generation
route.hard_comment: Rated 12b/c?, new line left of Elders of the Tribe. Techy cruxes. would be 5 star except for finish slab.
route.fair_comment: Not too hard if you have the wing span.

route.name: Void Warrior
route.hard_comment: start move

route.name: Thrill Jill
route.hard_comment: slab

route.name: The Warden
route.soft_comment: In retrospect, maybe Texas Sevan is 8a too? Or maybe this is easier?

route.name: *San Quentin
route.soft_comment: This 13c extension makes a significant bump from big house. Fought tooth and nail! Very surprised to make it to the end. At 3 different spots I thought I was going to fly off. Pysched.

route.name: Felon
route.hard_comment: Very bouldery and crimpy crux at the third bolt to a huge rest midway up and another powerful crux involving underclings and blocky pinches near the top. Pretty fun and under-repeated route at Jailhouse. I think the super crimpy lower crux scares some of the sport climbers away. Boulderer's delight. Used to be 13a but there are too many good rests so consensus 12d.
route.fair_comment: stuck the undercling with 2 fingers but battled it out at the end of the day!
route.soft_comment: Fell off trying the wrong beta at the top on the flash! Fun route!

route.name: Enemy Combatant
route.soft_comment: Thanks Vian, Ginny, and that guy I went with that one day. 7th.

route.name: *Blacklisted
route.fair_comment: 2nd ascent. Great line that doesn't see a lot of traffic. Bouldery and short 12b with a massive rest at the first anchors then continue several more bolts on the neighboring 12c to finish. Long! Thanks to Vian for all the great beta and suggesting I continue into the extension after flashing the first part!!!
route.soft_comment: hardest flash so far. thanks for the beta, Matt!

route.name: Flower Power
route.soft_comment: Amazing, 4th red-point attempt. 3rd go of the day.

route.name: Tossed Salad
route.fair_comment: Linkup of soap into tower of power extension. 2nd ascent.
route.soft_comment: Silly link up with silly name. But surprisingly fun climbing.

route.name: Hacktivism
route.fair_comment: Felt awesome today. All that bouldering is good for something I guess!! This route seems much harder than any other 8c at the House.

route.name: Public Burning
route.fair_comment: attacking the project from multiple sides. fun to take common thug to the top.
route.soft_comment: Sort of a silly link up but I'm psyched. Fun.

route.name: Early release
route.fair_comment: After struggling with my shoulder for nearly a year, I feel as though I'm starting to get back in shape. I've been repeating a number of climbs at the local crag to build strength, but this is one of the first new ones. Nice to stretch my limbs on something new :) Short and bouldery.

route.name: Lethal Injection
route.hard_comment: Hard for me; 1 low percentage move in the middle of great rock climbing. So glad to have it dry!
route.fair_comment: Fun, steep climbing, but mediocre rock quality. 4 tries...
route.soft_comment: Lucky number seventh go. Both cruxes were wet. a very nice 20 meter steep climb with the crux at the top. too bad this little gem stays wet half the year.

route.name: Hang Time
route.soft_comment: nice padless diversion from the 50-bar project

route.name: Hard Time
route.fair_comment: Kneebar Boulder problem to 5.12b. Fun! Lil soft- hard to figure out the sideways right Kneebar into left toe hook than left drop knee
route.soft_comment: 3 goes. Two hardish moves into a kneebar you could make lunch in followed by some fun slightly heady movement.

route.name: Violated
route.soft_comment: Bouldery/Short

route.name: Iron Junky

route.soft_comment: after BKA

route.soft_comment: Pumpy

route.name: Dead Man Walking

route.soft_comment: 9 tries/bad beta. Thanks Mike.

route.name: Insecurity
route.hard_comment: Approximately 43,567 atttempts

route.soft_comment: Great route, new fav on the left side

route.name: Bulimia
route.fair_comment: Finally Sent this thing today after a lot of work over the years. Took a while to find good beta and even with it the crux is quite hard. Originally a 12c in the guidebook it's possible holds have broken since the FA or perhaps it was sandbagged to begin with. Either way a sampling of any 12c in the park compared with this will leave no doubts that this is for sure more difficult. As this route is essentially just a V6 or V7 boulder problem with a few hard moves at the start and some easy but "don't blow it" moves at the end I think 12d or 13a is fair. Since this is a crimpy route and crimps are my style though, and considering that it took 5 attempts today and probably 25 to 30 attempts over the last two years I think it's far more likely to be 13a than 12d and 13a is what I'm giving it here. Regardless of grade this is a very fun route that deserves more traffic than it currently gets.
